**Cooldown Timer**
================

### Overview

A simple cooldown timer that prevents an action from being performed within a specified time period.

### Code

```javascript
class CooldownTimer {
  constructor(cooldown) {
    this.cooldown = cooldown;
    this.lastActivation = 0;
  }

  isReady() {
    const currentTime = Date.now();
    return currentTime - this.lastActivation >= this.cooldown;
  }

  activate() {
    if (this.isReady()) {
      this.lastActivation = Date.now();
      return true;
    }
    return false;
  }
}
```

### Usage

```javascript
const cooldownTimer = new CooldownTimer(5000); // 5-second cooldown

// Check if the cooldown is ready
if (cooldownTimer.isReady()) {
  console.log("Cooldown is ready");
  cooldownTimer.activate(); // Activate the cooldown
} else {
  console.log("Cooldown is not ready yet");
}

// Wait for 5 seconds
